            "name": "Yehoshua Heshil Miro",
            "bio": "Yehoshua Heshil ben Rabbi Binyamin Miro (fl. first-half 19th c.) was a writer and Jewish educator in Prussia, an early advocate and teacher of Jewish girls. He worked as a professor at a private school, and a teacher at the <a href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Königliche_Wilhelms-Schule\">Königliche Wilhelms-Schule</a> (and possibly also the <a href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Industrieschule_für_israelitische_Mädchen\">Industrial School for Israelite Girls</a>), in then Prussian Breslau. We know very little else about Miro aside from his publication of a popular anthology of teḥinot for German speaking women first published in 1829. If you know more about Miro, please <a href=\"/contact/\">contact us</a>.",
            "website": "",
            "avatar": "https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Keith-Evans-Green-Tree-Yellow-Field-CC-BY-SA-250x250.jpg",
            "profile_link": "https://opensiddur.org/profile/yehoshua-heshil-miro"
